snippet.textDisplay: I love orange hair! I had orange hair for October. I’m hoping you or someone in the comments can help me with something. I went blonde a few weeks ago and chopped about six inches off to celebrate getting a new job. I was expecting a blonde with violet undertones (I used the clairol true color line and mixed a 6AV with a 10AV). I feel like it turned out very ashy (my base was a really light blonde with slight yellow tones, I’d say about a level 10 or 11). I would like to use purple shampoo, but I’m very worried that my hair will turn green. Could I use a red semi permanent on wet hair as a toner and rinse after a minute or two? Or will my hair be fine with a purple shampoo? I’ve never been a legit blonde before(aka rocked piss yellow hair, never used toner, never used purple shampoo 🤣). Would appreciate feedback 💜 p.s I’ve been binge watching your videos since I discovered you on Facebook ❤️

snippet.textDisplay: What is your opinion on Henna / Mehendi? Before you're confused by Google search, let me tell you Henna is a natural dye obtained from Henna plants leaf and has been used for dying  hair and hands / feet since ancient times. It's famous in India and Arab countries as it can naturally color your hair black/ brown / red / orange if you master it's composition. It's commonly used in my family as a hair mask as it helps with dandruff and helps strengthen and nourish the hair. The only down side is it's cold properties, so if you're easily susceptible to a cold, you might need some precautions. As for genral public like me, as long as I give myself ample sunlight after the wash, it'll be fine. Just wash off Henna early morning and sun dry your hair and it'll all be fine. This has been in our family for generations and am totally fine with it. Unless you get a chemically formulated version of Henna whose effects entirely depends on their composition. Would like to know your opinion as a non asian

snippet.textDisplay: Hi Braid!! My names Kaitlin and I’m 22 years old. I am the only one in my family with curly hair. I really tight natural curls but my hair is always frizzy and I can never seem to figure out what to do to take care of it correctly. I’ve always absolutely hated my hair. I’ve never liked my hair, ever, and it’s always a constant battle. I’ve spent hours crying over it. I’ve chopped it all off twice now to try to “give it a fresh start” of sorts. I’ve tried a million different things and no matter what, I hate it. I don’t like to look in the mirror because I just hate how my hair looks. I find myself just putting it up in a bun because of how much I dislike the way it looks down and that only damages it and makes it worse. I was wondering if you could do a curly hair 101 video — Washing, styling and general curly hair care. I know there are a bunch of different curl types so it would be impossible to cater to them all, but anything would help. I don’t even know what curl type I have to be honest because it looks different every day depending on several factors. Thank you for reading this, if you got to see it!! 😊😊

snippet.textDisplay: Why do I want orange hair now?
snippet.textOriginal: Why do I want orange hair now?

snippet.textDisplay:
Why the stereotype that people don't like orange hair? A lot of people like funky colours and orange included. An orange hair is beautiful, like Irish people, and when I was little I like the Anna from the Green Gable hair. But in the story, she was made fun by boys saying she are carrot head. I think it's the American stereotype to not like orange hair.

On another note, as someone who are born with Asian black hair, black eyes, coarse hair, dark brown skin, and when I was in school basically everyone has the same colour black and not other colours at all except maybe some chinese has a little lighter brown black hair (in convent school, so dyeing hair is prohibited 😅) -- any other colour on people's eyes and hair is beautiful to me, blue eyes, green eyes, blonde hair, auburn hair, ginger all are beautiful and admirable that I wish I have that kinda hair 😁

Then I grow up an as adult I have friends from all over the world and see those colours real life, yes they are beautiful, but then I found out white people colour their hairs too to others...so I'm like nahhh that's not original. And embraced my black hair black eyes more now 😁
